Sorry folks, I got so excited talking to a real live military man with a helluva brain, been chatting directly with hackworth, he answers his own e mail, that I forgot to add this to the above post.  Perhaps there is a mutual ground where the Cooks and the Commies, The Spatz's and the Pack, can work together, for our country, and our children, or am I being blindsided by the Flag?  I would like all of your reactions, not to me, but to Hack and his movement. (please)<br><br>
&quot;Thousands of our readers have now joined SOLDIERS FOR THE TRUTH. Many of these good people have also written, volunteering their time and money.<br><br>
Here's where we are. The SFTT Foundation's legal paperwork has been approved (To have hired a law firm would have cost a few thousand dollars. But Keith McWilliams, a retired Brig. General and a California lawyer, did all the legal work pro bono, even put up his own dollars to pay the necessary fees to get things up and running.)<br><br>
We don't have our tax exempt status yet, so we are not accepting tax deductible donations until after the first of the year. Thanks to all of you who have sent money. We will hold this money in trust until after the first of the year. After that date checks should be made payable to Soldiers For The Truth Foundation and mailed to: 3008 Doeg Indian Court, Alexandria, VA  22309<br><br>
So, the SFTT Foundation is set to cross the line of departure on 1 January 1998. We'll set up near the Pentagon, so we'll be better able to keep an eye on that slick institution and our even slicker and sicker Congress. <br><br>
Many of our readers have asked: Do I have to be a Vet or a serving member of the armed forces to join? Answer: Membership is about -- DEFENDING AMERICA SMARTLY, STOPPING THE PENTAGON WASTE, PREVENTING MORE VIETNAMS AND SOMALIAS AND CAUSING CONGRESS TO PROVIDE AMERICA WITH A LEAN AND REFORMED MILITARY MACHINE. <br><br>
Membership is open to all who want to make this happen.<br><br>
Until SFTT finds an old garage or an unused missile silo in Virginia to set up in, we'll continue to do our thing from Montana and Arizona (Arizona-based Joe Beranek, my great Ops Sgt from Vietnam, has volunteered to become our unpaid NEWSLETTER deputy editor). <br><br>
Until Virginia is good to go, all SFTT activities -- NEWSLETTER, HACK'S COLUMN, SNAILMAIL, RADIO/TV PROGRAMS, PROVIDING LEADS AND BREAKING STORIES TO THE MEDIA -- will continue to be done here in Montana.<br><br>
Please be patient. We'll get our act together once we hack our way through all the red tape. <br><br>
Thanks much for your support. Once we have the numbers, the muscle, we can lean on those responsible and get our defense machine running effectively, economically and smoothly again.<br><br>
Carl, Hack, Keith and Roger&quot; <br><br>
doc spatz
